post_text: At CCMS we worked on goal setting as a building last year. This was not teacher led, rather student driven. Mr. Houser‚Äôs class set a goal of EVERY student will reach 85% or higher on their unit test. He was happy when the whole group reached their class goal. Most, not only reached the 85 but they surpassed their goal. So today after a long break, our now 7th graders got to tape Mr. Houser to the wall. To say they were a bit excited, would certainly be an understatement! Something Mr. Houser noticed was when they set their goal together they started working more together and he witnessed them encouraging one another more.This is just another example of how our team goes ALL IN for our/your kidsüêæ #TigerLegacy

May 17 at 8:46 AM ¬∑

Today, Sunday, May 17, 2020 our PHS Senior Class should be walking down the aisle to Pomp and Circumstance, but instead most of them will be celebrating at home with their families. This celebration should also be shared with friends that hug each other and reminisce about the good times of their past years of school days. Some will follow paths that may take them away from old friends from Plattsburg. Many will pursue working careers, while some may be entering the military along with the many others planning on college for the next four years. Think of them today and remember they are ‚ÄúPHS STRONG‚Äù! Their journey has been temporarily put on hold during these difficult times but because of their strength and courage we now know that they can conquer anything!

So today our Burg celebrates ‚ÄúYOU‚Äù the ‚ÄúSTRONG PHS GRADUATES of 2020‚Äù! Celebrate like you have never celebrated ever before because you deserve for today to be ‚ÄúYOUR DAY‚Äù! CONGRATULATIONS CLASS OF 2020!‚ù§Ô∏èüêØüñ§

We hope you enjoyed our game of "Guess Who?". Here are all the answers for you!
https://spark.adobe.com/video/4brzUBw9XwHZ7

We had some amazing guessers our there, everyone answered 100% correct on almost 25% of the 34 guesses (Mericle, Bearly, Filger, Turner, Kirk, Thomas, Harris & Burton).

Thanks to everyone that played! Alivia & Nathan Lloyd, Kim McClain (Ms. Mimi), Braelan Waltersheidt, Jackson Hall, Mrs. Chappell (student teacher), Karlie Florence, Kallie Townsend, Xander Burton & Gavin Ralston! I also kept it secret from all my teachers üòú who almost all guess correctly! I think they know they're co-workers well!

Way to go -
--Karlie Florence got 31 out of 34 correct!
--Kallie Townsend got all but 1 that she guessed correct!
AWESOME JOB!

CONGRATS to Xander B & Gavin R. for guess 100% correctly!!

shared_text:
CCR-3 Speech/Language
March 17 at 4:03 PM ¬∑

1. Progress Notes should all be archived and available on the Parent Portal on Lumen. If you do not see it, let me know. If you need a copy emailed to you, let me know and I can email you. Fun fact: you should be able to see IEPs and Evaluation Reports there as well, I've been told!

2. See attached graphic regarding what will happen with speech and language IF school is cancelled for an extended period. I know just as much as you, and right now school is still scheduled for next week. We are still working through logistics of how it would look and will keep you updated if school cancellations were to occur, so stay tuned to social media. I will be available regularly via email if you have any questions, or feel free to message me any time through ParentSquare or Seesaw.

I will be in touch! Stay healthy and everyone enjoy your Spring Break!
